The FCT minister, Muhammad Musa Bello, has condoled with the immediate former House of Representatives member for Abuja South Federal Constituency, Alhaji Zakari Angulu Dobi, over the death of his father, Alhaji Adamu Angulu. Bello, who paid a condolence visit to the family in Dobi, was accompanied by the state APC chairman, Alhaji Usman Abdulmalik, Alhaji Musa Tanko, Alhaji Ishaku Tanko Yamawo, and FCT Permanent Secretary, Chief Chinyeaka Oha’a. The minister, who joined other Muslim residents of the community for the funeral prayers for the deceased, said he was saddened over the death. He urged the family of the deceased to see the death as designed by God and also prayed for Allah to give them the fortitude to bear the loss. Alhaji Zakari Angulu Dobi thanked the minister and other stakeholders for the visit. Paikon-Kore loses district head ...As FCT minister presents flags to Jisalo, Dobi, G’lada chair You’ll account for your actions,  Agora tells leaders Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin